msgid "Privacy Policy"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"How Snowdesk collects, uses, and protects your personal data. UK GDPR "
"privacy policy."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk &middot; snowdesk.info &middot; Effective 1 November 2026 &middot; "
"Version 1.0"
msgstr ""

msgid "The short version:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"We collect your email address only if you choose to subscribe to bulletin "
"notifications. We don't sell your data. We don't track you across the web. "
"We don't use advertising or analytics cookies."
msgstr ""

msgid "1. Who we are"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk is operated by Henri Tamboral, an individual based in London, UK. "
"Snowdesk is a free service that displays Swiss avalanche bulletins published "
"by the WSL Institute for Snow and Avalanche Research (SLF). There are no "
"employees; all operations are carried out by the sole operator."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Questions about this policy? Email: <a class=\"underline\" "
"href=\"mailto:privacy@snowdesk.info\">privacy@snowdesk.info</a>"
msgstr ""

msgid "2. What data we collect"
msgstr ""

msgid "2a. Subscriptions"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"If you subscribe to bulletin email notifications, we collect your email "
"address. That is the only personal data we ever ask for. We collect it only "
"when you actively sign up — we never collect it passively."
msgstr ""

msgid "2b. Location"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The interactive map can use your browser's optional geolocation to centre "
"the map on your current position. This happens entirely in your browser — "
"your location is never transmitted to or stored by Snowdesk."
msgstr ""

msgid "2c. Session data"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"We use a session cookie that is strictly necessary for the site to function. "
"It contains no personal information and expires when you close your browser. "
"No consent is required for this cookie under UK PECR."
msgstr ""

msgid "2d. Server logs"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Our server automatically records standard technical information when you "
"visit: your IP address, the page you requested, and the time of the request. "
"We use this only to keep the service running and to investigate errors. Logs "
"are retained for 14 days and then deleted."
msgstr ""

msgid "3. Why we use your data"
msgstr ""

msgid "We process your data under the following legal bases (UK GDPR):"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"<strong>Email address</strong> — consent. You gave it to us voluntarily when "
"you subscribed, and you can withdraw it at any time by unsubscribing."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"<strong>Session data and server logs</strong> — legitimate interest. We need "
"these to keep the service secure and operational."
msgstr ""

msgid "4. How long we keep your data"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"<strong>Email address</strong> — kept for as long as your subscription is "
"active. Deleted within 30 days of unsubscribing or on request."
msgstr ""

msgid "<strong>Location</strong> — never stored."
msgstr ""

msgid "<strong>Server logs</strong> — 14 days."
msgstr ""

msgid "5. Who we share your data with"
msgstr ""

msgid "We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data with anyone."
msgstr ""

msgid "We use a small number of trusted service providers to operate Snowdesk:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"<strong>Render</strong> (render.com) — hosts the Snowdesk servers. Your IP "
"address and request data pass through their infrastructure."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"<strong>Resend</strong> (resend.com) — sends your bulletin notification "
"emails. They receive your email address for this purpose only."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"<strong>Open-Meteo</strong> (open-meteo.com) — provides weather data "
"displayed on bulletin pages. No personal data is shared with them."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"<strong>SLF / WSL</strong> — provides the avalanche bulletin data. No "
"personal data is shared with them."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"All providers are contractually required to handle your data in compliance "
"with UK GDPR. We do not use any advertising networks or analytics platforms."
msgstr ""

msgid "6. Your rights"
msgstr ""

msgid "Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:"
msgstr ""

msgid "Access the personal data we hold about you"
msgstr ""

msgid "Correct inaccurate data"
msgstr ""

msgid "Request deletion of your data (&ldquo;right to be forgotten&rdquo;)"
msgstr ""

msgid "Object to processing"
msgstr ""

msgid "Withdraw consent at any time"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To exercise any of these rights, email <a class=\"underline\" "
"href=\"mailto:privacy@snowdesk.info\">privacy@snowdesk.info</a>. We will "
"respond within 30 days."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the UK Information "
"Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a class=\"underline\" href=\"https://"
"ico.org.uk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ico.org.uk</a>."
msgstr ""

msgid "7. Children"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk is a publicly accessible information service. We do not knowingly "
"collect personal data from children under 13. If you believe a child under "
"13 has subscribed, please contact us at <a class=\"underline\" "
"href=\"mailto:privacy@snowdesk.info\">privacy@snowdesk.info</a> and we will "
"delete the data without delay."
msgstr ""

msgid "8. Cookies"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk uses one strictly necessary session cookie. It is set automatically "
"when you visit the site, contains no personal information, and expires when "
"you close your browser. Because it is strictly necessary, no consent banner "
"is required under UK PECR. We do not use tracking, analytics, or advertising "
"cookies of any kind."
msgstr ""

msgid "9. Changes to this policy"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"If we make material changes to this policy, we will update the effective "
"date at the top and notify subscribers by email. Continued use of Snowdesk "
"after changes constitutes acceptance."
msgstr ""

msgid "Terms"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk terms of use, data-licence acknowledgement, and liability "
"disclaimer."
msgstr ""

msgid "Terms of use"
msgstr ""

msgid "Data source and licence"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk renders avalanche bulletins published by the <a class=\"underline\" "
"href=\"https://www.slf.ch\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" >WSL "
"Institute for Snow and Avalanche Research SLF</a>. The underlying data is "
"licensed under <a class=\"underline\" href=\"https://creativecommons.org/"
"licenses/by/4.0/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" >CC BY 4.0</a>."
msgstr ""

msgid "Snowdesk is not a substitute for the official bulletin"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk renders avalanche bulletins published by SLF. It is an information "
"service only — it does not replace the official SLF bulletin, professional "
"avalanche training, or your own assessment of conditions in the field. "
"Always verify current conditions directly with SLF before venturing into "
"avalanche terrain."
msgstr ""

msgid "Always consult SLF and make your own on-site assessment"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Avalanche conditions change rapidly and vary with aspect, elevation, and "
"recent weather. No digital service can capture every local hazard. Before "
"entering avalanche terrain, check the official SLF bulletin at <a "
"class=\"underline\" href=\"https://www.avalanches.org\" target=\"_blank\" "
"rel=\"noopener\" >avalanches.org</a>, seek current local knowledge, and make "
"your own on-site assessment. Your safety is your responsibility."
msgstr ""

msgid "Limitation of liability"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To the maximum extent permitted by law, Snowdesk and its operator shall not "
"be liable for any loss, injury, or damage arising from your use of, or "
"reliance on, information displayed on this site. Snowdesk is provided \"as "
"is\", without warranties of any kind, including accuracy, timeliness, or "
"completeness."
msgstr ""

msgid "SLF's own no-liability clause"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Per the SLF <a class=\"underline\" href=\"https://www.slf.ch/en/services-and-"
"products/slf-data-service/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" >data-"
"service terms of use</a>, SLF makes bulletin data available for information "
"purposes only and accepts no liability for the delivery of that data or for "
"decisions made on the basis of it."
msgstr ""

msgid "Terms of Service"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk Terms of Service — what the service is, how to use it safely, and "
"the legal terms that apply."
msgstr ""

msgid "Plain English first:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk is a free avalanche information service. It does not replace the "
"official SLF bulletin, professional avalanche training, or your own "
"judgement in the mountains. Your safety is your responsibility."
msgstr ""

msgid "1. About Snowdesk"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk is operated by Henri Tamboral (\"I\", \"me\", \"my\"), an "
"individual based in London, UK. Snowdesk displays Swiss avalanche bulletins "
"published by the WSL Institute for Snow and Avalanche Research (SLF) and "
"provides optional email notifications for subscribed regions. There are no "
"employees; the service is run entirely by the sole operator."
msgstr ""

msgid "2. Acceptance of terms"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"By accessing Snowdesk at snowdesk.info, you agree to these Terms of Service. "
"If you do not agree, please do not use the service."
msgstr ""

msgid "3. The service"
msgstr ""

msgid "Snowdesk provides:"
msgstr ""

msgid "A viewer for Swiss avalanche bulletins published by SLF"
msgstr ""

msgid "An interactive map showing current avalanche danger ratings by region"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Optional email notifications when new bulletins are published for subscribed "
"regions"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk is provided free of charge. I reserve the right to change, suspend, "
"or discontinue any part of the service at any time without notice."
msgstr ""

msgid "4. Safety — please read this"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Avalanche bulletins are a forecast tool, not a guarantee of safe conditions. "
"Snowdesk is an information service only — it does not replace the official "
"SLF bulletin, professional avalanche training, or your own assessment of "
"conditions in the field."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Avalanche conditions change rapidly and vary with aspect, elevation, and "
"recent weather. No digital service can capture every local hazard."
msgstr ""

msgid "Before entering avalanche terrain, you should:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Check the official SLF bulletin at <a class=\"underline\" href=\"https://"
"www.avalanches.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" >avalanches.org</a>"
msgstr ""

msgid "Seek current local knowledge from guides, hut keepers, or ski patrol"
msgstr ""

msgid "Make your own on-site assessment of conditions"
msgstr ""

msgid "Your safety in the mountains is your own responsibility."
msgstr ""

msgid "5. Intellectual property"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk's original content — including the interface, design, and copy — is "
"owned by Henri Tamboral. You may view it for personal, non-commercial use. "
"You may not reproduce, redistribute, or republish it without permission."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The avalanche bulletin data displayed on Snowdesk is published by the <a "
"class=\"underline\" href=\"https://www.slf.ch\" target=\"_blank\" "
"rel=\"noopener\" >WSL Institute for Snow and Avalanche Research SLF</a> and "
"licensed under <a class=\"underline\" href=\"https://creativecommons.org/"
"licenses/by/4.0/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" >CC BY 4.0</a>. That "
"data remains SLF's intellectual property."
msgstr ""

msgid "6. Email subscriptions"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You can subscribe to receive email notifications when new avalanche "
"bulletins are published for one or more Swiss regions. To subscribe, you "
"provide your email address. By subscribing you agree to receive those "
"notifications."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"You can unsubscribe at any time by clicking the unsubscribe link in any "
"email we send you. We will not send you anything other than bulletin "
"notifications and essential service messages."
msgstr ""

msgid "7. Acceptable use"
msgstr ""

msgid "You agree not to:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Scrape or republish SLF bulletin data commercially without SLF's permission "
"(the data is licensed under CC BY 4.0 and remains SLF's property)"
msgstr ""

msgid "Attempt to gain unauthorised access to Snowdesk's systems or data"
msgstr ""

msgid "Use the service in any way that violates applicable law"
msgstr ""

msgid "8. Limitation of liability"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"To the maximum extent permitted by law, Snowdesk and its operator shall not "
"be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential loss "
"arising from your use of — or inability to use — this service. This "
"includes, without limitation, any decisions made on the basis of avalanche "
"information displayed on Snowdesk."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Snowdesk is provided \"as is\" without warranties of any kind, including "
"accuracy, timeliness, or fitness for a particular purpose."
msgstr ""

msgid "9. Governing law"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"These terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any disputes "
"shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and "
"Wales."
msgstr ""

msgid "10. Changes to these terms"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"We may update these terms from time to time. We will update the effective "
"date at the top. Continued use of Snowdesk after changes constitutes "
"acceptance of the revised terms."
msgstr ""

msgid "11. Contact"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Questions about these terms? Email: <a class=\"underline\" "
"href=\"mailto:privacy@snowdesk.info\">privacy@snowdesk.info</a>"
msgstr ""

